# Security Guidelines

Cursor does not enforce permissions at the IDE level. Adherence to these guidelines is a behavioral commitment that protects the project's security posture.

## Commands — NEVER execute

- Network: `curl`, `wget`, `nc`, `ncat`, `netcat`, `ssh`, `scp`, `sftp`, `rsync`
- Privilege escalation: `sudo`, `su`, `doas`, `pkexec`, `runuser`, `newgrp`
- Destructive: `chmod 777`, `rm -rf`
- Temp/scheduling: `mktemp`, `crontab`, `at`
- System management: `systemctl`, `service`
- Containers/cloud: `docker`, `podman`, `kubectl`, `terraform`, `aws`, `gcloud`, `az`
- Code execution: `python3 -c`, `python3 -m http.server`, `eval`, `exec`
- Shell config: `source /etc/*`, `source ~/.bashrc`, `source ~/.zshrc`

## Commands — ASK the user before executing

- `git push`
- `git rebase`
- `git reset`
- `git merge`

## Files — NEVER read

- `.env`, `.env.*`
- `secrets/**`
- `*.pem`, `*.key`, `*.p12`, `*.pfx`
- `~/.ssh/**`, `~/.aws/**`, `~/.azure/**`, `~/.kube/**`, `~/.gnupg/**`
- `~/.docker/config.json`, `~/.netrc`
- `/etc/passwd`, `/etc/shadow`, `/etc/sudoers`

## Files — NEVER edit

- `.git/**`
- `/etc/**`, `/usr/**`, `/bin/**`
- `~/.bashrc`, `~/.zshrc`, `~/.profile`, `~/.ssh/**`

## Web fetching — DISABLED

Do not fetch external URLs.

## Telemetry

Disable telemetry when available. Do not send data to external services unless explicitly requested.
